## Did you know?

* If you ingested your data using ArcGIS Pro or ArcGIS Online, you can add additional datasets using the ArcGIS Living Atlas. (LINK out to Finding Data Resources and the Living Atlas).  

* In ArcGIS Online, you can also drag and drop your data file directly onto the map, which will add it to your content under **My Content**.  

* In QGIS, you can add publicly hosted data on ArcGIS Online through the ArcGIS Rest Server (https://docs.qgis.org/3.44/en/docs/user\_manual/managing\_data\_source/opening\_data.html).  

* In the Contents pane (ArcGIS) or Layers List (QGIS), polygon layers toward the top will obscure layers listed beneath. You can drag and drop polygon layers to the bottom of the list so that they are not covering up your other data.  
## Troubleshooting

* **Coordinate System and Projection Errors**:   
  * Missing or Wrong CRS: If you load tabular data (like a CSV with XY coordinates) and points do not plot in the correct location or fail to draw, your CRS is likely mismatched. Confirm the data's inherent coordinate system and ensure your map view uses the same system   
* **Corrupt Geometry:**   
  * Check Geometry: Some features may have corrupt, null, or looping geometries.  
  * The Fix:  
    * ArcGIS Online: There is no native tool to fix corrupt geometry. You must download the data and repair it manually or in ArcGIS Pro.  
    * ArcGIS Pro: Run the **Check Geometry** tool to identify errors, then run Repair Geometry to fix invalid features   
    * QGIS: Run the **Fix Geometries** tool, found in Processing \> Toolbox.  
* **Attribute Table Errors ("Could Not Load Data"):**   
  * Failed to load rows: If the map draws the features but the attribute table fails to open or returns a "Could not load data" error, there may be schema mismatches or bad spatial indexes.   
  * The Fix:  
    * ArcGIS Online: Download the data and review [attribute table errors](https://support.esri.com/en-us/knowledge-base/accessing-data-failed-000016280), check to see if you have null values or unsupported characters   
    * ArcGIS Pro: Recalculate the spatial index for the feature class or export the features into a new File Geodatabase    
    * QGIS:   
      * To fix a “No Spatial Index” error, run the **Create spatial index** tool.  
      * For schema issues, install and run the **Table Structure Compare** plugin.

